The specific epithet is named for Stanley H. Weitzman, in recognition of his seminal work on the systematics of Neotropical characiforms, particularly of the characid subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eigenmann" authorityYear="1914" box="[267,464,483,506]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Glandulocaudinae">Glandulocaudinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
